============================================
|ID|OPERATOR           |NAME|EST. ROWS|COST|
--------------------------------------------
|0 |EXCHANGE IN DISTR  |    |8        |38  |
|1 | EXCHANGE OUT DISTR|    |8        |38  |
|2 |  WINDOW FUNCTION  |    |8        |38  |
|3 |   TABLE SCAN      |t1  |8        |37  |
============================================

Outputs & filters: 
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([t1.a], [t1.b], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)]), filter(nil)
  1 - output([t1.a], [t1.b], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)]), filter(nil)
  2 - output([t1.a], [t1.b], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)]), filter(nil), 
      win_expr(T_FUN_COUNT(1)), partition_by([t1.a], [t1.b]), order_by(nil), window_type(RANGE), upper(UNBOUNDED PRECEDING), lower(UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING)
      win_expr(T_FUN_COUNT(1)), partition_by([t1.a]), order_by(nil), window_type(RANGE), upper(UNBOUNDED PRECEDING), lower(UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING)
  3 - output([t1.a], [t1.b]), filter(nil), 
      access([t1.a], [t1.b]), partitions(p[0-3])

explain select a, b, count(1) over(partition by a,b), count(1) over(partition by a,b,c) from t2;
