explain select a, b, count(1) over(partition by a) from t2;
Query Plan
======================================================
|ID|OPERATOR                     |NAME|EST. ROWS|COST|
------------------------------------------------------
|0 |WINDOW FUNCTION              |    |2000     |1004|
|1 | EXCHANGE IN TASK ORDER DISTR|    |2000     |622 |
|2 |  EXCHANGE OUT DISTR         |    |2000     |433 |
|3 |   TABLE SCAN                |t2  |2000     |433 |
======================================================

Outputs & filters: 
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([t2.a], [t2.b], [T_FUN_COUNT(1)]), filter(nil), 
      win_expr(T_FUN_COUNT(1)), partition_by([t2.a]), order_by(nil), window_type(RANGE), upper(UNBOUNDED PRECEDING), lower(UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING)
  1 - output([t2.a], [t2.b]), filter(nil), task_order
  2 - output([t2.a], [t2.b]), filter(nil)
  3 - output([t2.a], [t2.b]), filter(nil), 
      access([t2.a], [t2.b]), partitions(p[0-1])

drop database if exists wf;
